article.headline: Holy Cross 64, Lafayette 50
article.story: EASTON, Pa. -- Andrew Keister had 16 points and 10 rebounds to lead Holy Cross to a 64-50 win over Lafayette on Saturday. Keister, who was 7-7 from the field and 2-2 at the foul line, led four Holy Cross (12-11) players in double figures. R.J. Evans had 11 and Andrew Beinert and Colin Cunningham each had 10. Ryan Willen led the way for Lafayette with 17 points. Andrew Brown added 12, but also committed five turnovers. The teams were tied at 30 at the end of the first half. But Holy Cross shot 50 percent from the field in the second half, compared to 26 percent for Lafayette (6-17). Holy Cross also dominated in the paint with 32 points, compared to 12 for Lafayette.
